import React, { Component } from 'react'; import { connect } from 'react-redux' import Fade from 'react-reveal/Fade' class UserDetails extends Component { constructor() { super() this.state = { email: "", password: "", firstName: "", lastName: "", } } onChange(e) { this.setState({ [e.target.name]: e.target.value }) } render() { let date = "" const user = this.props.editUser && this.props.editUser.user if (user && user.dob) { let temp = new Date(Date.parse(user.dob)) date = temp.toISOString() } return (
this.onChange} type="email" name="email" className="form-control w-100" id="email" value={this.state.email ? this.state.email : null} placeholder={user ? user.email : "Enter email"} />
this.onChange} type="password" name="password" className="form-control w-100" id="password" value={this.state.password ? this.state.password : null} placeholder={user ? user.password : "Password"}/>
this.onChange} type="text" name="firstName" className="form-control w-100" id="firstName" aria-describedby="emailHelp" placeholder={user ? user.firstName : "First Name"}/>
this.onChange} type="text" name="lastName" className="form-control w-100" id="lastName" placeholder={user ? user.lastName : "Last Name"} />
this.onChange} value={this.state.dob} type="date" className="form-control" id="inputAddress2" name="dob" placeholder={date ? date : ""} />
{/*
this.onChange} value={this.state.picture} type="file" className="form-control" id="inputAddress2" name="picture" placeholder={user ? user.picture : ""} />
*/}
); } } const mapStateToProps = state => ({ editUser: state.temp.editUser, editUserType: state.temp.editUserType }) export default connect(mapStateToProps, {})(UserDetails);
